<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="498" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,724,1146]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,724,749]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Discussion</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[343,483,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Comefulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[343,483,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Comefulvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Carvalho" authorityName="Carvalho" box="[711,949,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Incafulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[711,835,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Incafulvius</emphasis>
Carvalho
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bergroth" authorityName="Bergroth" box="[1011,1264,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Xenocylapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1011,1154,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Xenocylapus</emphasis>
Bergroth
</taxonomicName>
in sharing the peculiar, very long and thin labium, with the segment I very short, not reaching the middle of the gula and with segment II much longer than segments III and IV (
<figureCitation box="[757,830,796,821]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,195,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[222,1369,195,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Comefulvius chingonus: 1, 3, 5, 7. Male holotype from Argentina. 2, 4, 6, 8: Male from Ecuador. 1 – 2. Habitus in dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm. 3 – 4. Head in dorsal view. 5 – 6. Pronotum in dorsal view. 7 – 8. Body in lateral view. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226597/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Fig. 
<number box="[814,830,797,821]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[847,1020,796,821]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. (1976) Mirideos neotropicais, CCII: Um novo genero e cinco especies novas da colecao da Academia de Ciencias da California (Hemiptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 36, 715 - 721." type="journal article" year="1976">
Carvalho 
<number box="[961,1020,796,821]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; van 
<bibRefCitation author="Doesburg" box="[1088,1267,796,821]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refString="Doesburg van, P. H. (1985) A new species of Xenocylapus Bergroth, 1922, from Surinam (Heteroptera, Miridae, Cylapinae). Entomologische Berichten, 45, 123 - 127." type="journal article" year="1985">
Doesburg 
<number box="[1207,1267,796,821]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1283,1354,796,821]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,195,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[222,1369,195,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Comefulvius chingonus: 1, 3, 5, 7. Male holotype from Argentina. 2, 4, 6, 8: Male from Ecuador. 1 – 2. Habitus in dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm. 3 – 4. Head in dorsal view. 5 – 6. Pronotum in dorsal view. 7 – 8. Body in lateral view. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226597/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Fig. 
<number box="[1338,1354,796,821]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Such distinctive shape of the labium clearly delimits these three genera as a distinct group within 
<taxonomicName box="[1315,1432,833,858]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cylapinae">Cylapinae</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName box="[306,446,868,893]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Comefulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[306,446,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Comefulvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares with 
<taxonomicName box="[590,714,868,893]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Incafulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[590,714,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Incafulvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[772,915,868,893]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Xenocylapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[772,915,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Xenocylapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the lack of the scent gland efferent system of the metepisternum; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[377,548,905,930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. (1976) Mirideos neotropicais, CCII: Um novo genero e cinco especies novas da colecao da Academia de Ciencias da California (Hemiptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 36, 715 - 721." type="journal article" year="1976">
Carvalho 
<number box="[488,548,905,930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Wolski pers. obs.) and the absence of costal fracture (
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[1175,1348,905,930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. (1976) Mirideos neotropicais, CCII: Um novo genero e cinco especies novas da colecao da Academia de Ciencias da California (Hemiptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 36, 715 - 721." type="journal article" year="1976">
Carvalho 
<number box="[1288,1348,905,930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1361,1429,905,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,195,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[222,1369,195,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Comefulvius chingonus: 1, 3, 5, 7. Male holotype from Argentina. 2, 4, 6, 8: Male from Ecuador. 1 – 2. Habitus in dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm. 3 – 4. Head in dorsal view. 5 – 6. Pronotum in dorsal view. 7 – 8. Body in lateral view. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226597/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Fig. 
<number box="[1414,1429,905,929]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
; van 
<bibRefCitation author="Doesburg" box="[198,373,941,966]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refString="Doesburg van, P. H. (1985) A new species of Xenocylapus Bergroth, 1922, from Surinam (Heteroptera, Miridae, Cylapinae). Entomologische Berichten, 45, 123 - 127." type="journal article" year="1985">
Doesburg 
<number box="[313,373,941,966]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[384,448,941,966]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,195,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[222,1369,195,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Comefulvius chingonus: 1, 3, 5, 7. Male holotype from Argentina. 2, 4, 6, 8: Male from Ecuador. 1 – 2. Habitus in dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm. 3 – 4. Head in dorsal view. 5 – 6. Pronotum in dorsal view. 7 – 8. Body in lateral view. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226597/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Fig. 
<number box="[435,448,941,965]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[473,613,941,966]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Comefulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[473,613,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Comefulvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[810,953,941,966]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Xenocylapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[810,953,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Xenocylapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in sharing the compact, strongly elongated and apically broad endosoma (
<figureCitation box="[517,592,977,1002]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,596,619]" captionTargetBox="[430,1154,156,572]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[427,1160,151,575]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Male genitalia of C. chingonus (specimen from Ecuador). 9. Endosoma (lateral view); 10 – 11. Left paramere (10: left lateral view; 11: dorsal view); 12. Right paramere (left lateral view). APR = apical process; BPR = basal process; DSS = sclerotized portion of ductus seminis inside endosoma; PB = paramere body." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226598/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Fig. 
<number box="[576,592,977,1001]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
; Wolski pers. obs.). 
<taxonomicName box="[844,984,977,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Comefulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[844,984,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Comefulvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1258,1382,977,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Incafulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1258,1382,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Incafulvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,294,1013,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Xenocylapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,294,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Xenocylapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the strongly elongated head, the shape of clypeus and the shape of pronotal callosities (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,195,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[222,1369,195,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Comefulvius chingonus: 1, 3, 5, 7. Male holotype from Argentina. 2, 4, 6, 8: Male from Ecuador. 1 – 2. Habitus in dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm. 3 – 4. Head in dorsal view. 5 – 6. Pronotum in dorsal view. 7 – 8. Body in lateral view. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226597/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Figs. 
<number box="[1387,1397,1013,1037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1.0">1</number>
–2, 5– 
<number box="[181,196,1049,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[207,376,1049,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. (1976) Mirideos neotropicais, CCII: Um novo genero e cinco especies novas da colecao da Academia de Ciencias da California (Hemiptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 36, 715 - 721." type="journal article" year="1976">
Carvalho 
<number box="[316,376,1049,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[386,452,1049,1074]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,195,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[222,1369,195,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Comefulvius chingonus: 1, 3, 5, 7. Male holotype from Argentina. 2, 4, 6, 8: Male from Ecuador. 1 – 2. Habitus in dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm. 3 – 4. Head in dorsal view. 5 – 6. Pronotum in dorsal view. 7 – 8. Body in lateral view. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226597/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Fig. 
<number box="[437,452,1049,1073]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
; van 
<bibRefCitation author="Doesburg" box="[512,687,1049,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refString="Doesburg van, P. H. (1985) A new species of Xenocylapus Bergroth, 1922, from Surinam (Heteroptera, Miridae, Cylapinae). Entomologische Berichten, 45, 123 - 127." type="journal article" year="1985">
Doesburg 
<number box="[627,687,1049,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[697,761,1049,1074]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,195,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[222,1369,195,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Comefulvius chingonus: 1, 3, 5, 7. Male holotype from Argentina. 2, 4, 6, 8: Male from Ecuador. 1 – 2. Habitus in dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm. 3 – 4. Head in dorsal view. 5 – 6. Pronotum in dorsal view. 7 – 8. Body in lateral view. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226597/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Fig. 
<number box="[748,761,1049,1073]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[784,924,1049,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Comefulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[784,924,1049,1074]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Comefulvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be also distinguished from both genera in possessing seven rows of punctures on the hemelytron (
<figureCitation box="[789,897,1085,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,195,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[222,1369,195,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Comefulvius chingonus: 1, 3, 5, 7. Male holotype from Argentina. 2, 4, 6, 8: Male from Ecuador. 1 – 2. Habitus in dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm. 3 – 4. Head in dorsal view. 5 – 6. Pronotum in dorsal view. 7 – 8. Body in lateral view. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226597/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Figs. 1, 6</figureCitation>
) whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[1015,1139,1085,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Incafulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1015,1139,1085,1110]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Incafulvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has one and 
<taxonomicName box="[1293,1436,1085,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Xenocylapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1293,1436,1085,1110]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Xenocylapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has three to five punctured hemelytral rows (
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[652,822,1121,1146]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. (1976) Mirideos neotropicais, CCII: Um novo genero e cinco especies novas da colecao da Academia de Ciencias da California (Hemiptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 36, 715 - 721." type="journal article" year="1976">
Carvalho 
<number box="[763,822,1121,1146]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; van 
<bibRefCitation author="Doesburg" box="[881,1057,1121,1146]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refString="Doesburg van, P. H. (1985) A new species of Xenocylapus Bergroth, 1922, from Surinam (Heteroptera, Miridae, Cylapinae). Entomologische Berichten, 45, 123 - 127." type="journal article" year="1985">
Doesburg 
<number box="[997,1057,1121,1146]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
